  "hypothesis": "HELM still had excess error at 24/18 and OLLB still looked constrained by a too-small final subset, so moving HELM to 24/22 and OLLB to 40/30 should improve the psychometric-default deterministic standing winner without reducing informative-source coverage or disturbing the OpenEval gain at 40/26.",
